"smart_sources:000 Zettelkasten/The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS)..md": {"path":"000 Zettelkasten/The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS)..md","class_name":"SmartSource","history":[{"blocks":{"000 Zettelkasten/The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS)..md#":true,"000 Zettelkasten/The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS)..md#The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS). [[Switchable CAR-T cells open the avenue to decrease the chance of toxicities such as CRS and neurotoxicity]] [[Universal CAR-T cell therapeutics overcome many of the barriers to widespread application and toxicities associated with this treatment.]] Another option to combat this issue are Bi-CAR T-cell therapies, where two antigens are used to direct the immunotherapeutic response onto tumour specific tissue. Clinical trials have also demonstrated that [[Bi-CAR T-cell therapy is less likely to cause severe onset of CRS and NT than Si-CAR therapies.]]{1}":true,"000 Zettelkasten/The most prevalent neurotoxicities that are a threat to patient health are cytokine release syndrome (CRS), macrophage activation syndrome, and immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity syndrome (ICANS)..md